items.title: Dimitri Vegas & Like Mike, Regard, Natti Natasha, SASH! - To The Beat
items.description:
Stream/download: https://orcd.co/tothebeat

‘To The Beat’ is a fresh new collaboration track coming hot off the press to Smash The House, featuring an unreal selection of artists. Not only do we have the label's head honchos and all-around party icons Dimitri Vegas & Like Mike, but they are joined by Deep House maestro Regard, the undeniable Natti Natasha, and German Pop legend Sash!. With these titans of the music world behind the wheel, ‘To The Beat’ is set to fly so high it will leave the stratosphere.
 
Taking elements from each artist's production style, 'To The Beat' is a unique blend of Trance, EDM, Pop, and House, all intertwined into a dancefloor anthem. Throughout the track is a fist pumping kick beat that acts as a foundation for Trance-styled synths and Natti Natasha’s high energy vocals. The song’s build-ups are quick, made with rolls of hats and claps with a dramatic pause before launching back into the thump of the beat. 
 
This latest project is the highly anticipated follow-up to the mega collaboration track ‘Thank You (Not So Bad)’. The smash hit saw  Dimitri Vegas & Like Mike  team up with the Dutch powerhouse Tiësto, the slick house duo W&W and the iconic Dido herself to put a dance spark into her classic ‘Thank You’. Released towards the end of 2023, it climbed high and remains in charts around the world today. Now, with ‘To The Beat’, the next step in the journey is set to be just as monumental, if not more.
 
‘To The Beat’ is a true collaboration of music VIPs; Dimitri Vegas & Like Mike are household names for any dance music fan. From claiming number 1 spots on the Top100DJs Poll to selling out hundreds of shows each year, there is little the pair cannot do. Regard is no stranger to success; his number one track ‘Ride It’ has accumulated over 1.3 billion streams on Spotify alone, and his other tracks are not far behind.
 
The vocals on the track are supplied by the Latin sensation Natti Natasha, an influential artist in her own right. Over the years, the Dominican singer has earned the accolades of most Top 10s on Billboard’s Latin Rhythm Airplay, 10 No. 1 singles, and dozens of gold and platinum plaques. The final puzzle piece is Sash!, one of the biggest success stories of German Pop music. For over 25 years, Sash! has been destroying dance floors and throughout this time has sold over 22 million albums worldwide and earned more than 65 Gold and Platinum awards.

items.title: Jody Wisternoff & Blake.08 - BLAM
items.description:
Buy/Stream: https://anjunabeats.ffm.to/jwbb.pbt
Listen to Anjunadeep New Releases: https://anjunadeep.co/newreleases.pbt
Discover the Anjunadeep Discography: https://anjunadeep.co/discog.pbt
Listen to Anjunadeep Radio 24/7: https://anjunadeep.co/radio.pbt
Release Date: 19th April 2024

Anjunadeep stalwart Jody Wisternoff teams up with rising Australian star Blake.08 for their debut collaborative single, ‘BLAM’; an atmospheric track featuring skippy UK drums, a dark, brooding bassline and a long suspenseful breakdown. 

Needing no introduction, Jody Wisternoff is the Bristol-based DJ and producer responsible for curating and mixing Anjunadeep flagship compilations alongside label-boss James Grant, as well as for seminal Anjunadeep albums such as his solo-debut 'Nightwhisper', and 'Tuesday Maybe' as part of duo Way Out West. Jody is a veteran of the global touring scene, including recently holding headline slots at premier Anjunadeep events such as Red Rocks, The Gorge and Finsbury Park London.

Sydney-based producer Blake.08 follows up on two previous Anjunadeep EPs that were incredibly well received by fans, and championed by James & Jody in Anjunadeep 14 last year with 'Eyes Ablaze', reimagining Blue Foundation's 'Eyes On Fire'. Blake.08 has recently played renowned Australian parties Lost Paradise festival, and Lost Sundays, as well as performing at Anjunadeep Sydney & Fiji in 2022.

'BLAM' is out now via Anjunadeep.
